NesPrgRom:3DC66:fief_to_mapid:[HIGH] Returns province_to_mapid_table[arg1] (arg1==0 passthrough; scenario_fief_count==50 selects extended path). Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3DC88:read_map_cell:[HIGH] sram_wrap read of a tactical map cell: $A57E + fief_to_mapid(battle_defending_province)*55 + row(arg2)*11 + col(arg1). The per-cell map source (matches the ROM->Map $A57E finding). Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3DCB2:generate_daimyo_name:[HIGH] Daimyo NAME GENERATOR: RNG-picks a row from each syllable table ($F930, $F95D), concatenates into a buffer, rejects duplicates vs daimyo_name_table ($77A8) via strcmp. The regenerator hypothesized in the $77A8 comment. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3DD81:init_new_daimyo_province_stats:[HIGH] Seeds a freshly-conquered province + new daimyo: daimyo byte = rng_mod(20)+20; per-field pct_op(rng+base) scaling; town($700D)+=50, rice($7013)+=50; $6D2D=20. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3DE78:select_message_string_de78:[MED] Selects a text/message pointer ($F720/$F72E/$796A) gated on $6DA1 bits 32/16 and a switch on arg1 in {7,13,23,30}. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3DEC1:reassign_fiefs_to_conqueror:[HIGH] Loops all fiefs; those owned by the defending daimyo get fief_to_daimyo_map[fief] = conqueror and $6DA2 cleared. Post-conquest ownership transfer. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3DF3D:daimyo_stat_transfer:[MED] +1 to daimyo-record fields +2/+4/+5 of arg1's daimyo, -1 to arg2's (stat handoff via fief_to_daimyo_record_addr). Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3DF73:transfer_force_triplet:[MED] 3-iteration copy of a word triplet (via scaled_transfer_da24) into the $7013 army/force region; selected->defending force transfer. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3DFBC:clamp_field_6d2d_to_30:[MED] For each tax-flagged fief (tax_helper_db12), caps the per-fief byte $6D2D at 30. ($6D2D unlabeled; init to 20 by init_new_daimyo_province_stats.) Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3DFFE:update_arms_table_dffe:[MED] local = arg2->arms/50 + 20; if $76AB[arg1] (stride 5) set, accumulate (old-new) into $76A9[arg1] and store local at $76AB[arg1]. Per-fief arms-delta bookkeeping. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3E03C:apply_conquest_outcome:[HIGH] Post-battle conquest orchestrator: rewrites the defending province stats from battle scratch ($6F7D-$6F87), updates fief_to_daimyo_map, calls daimyo_stat_transfer + reassign/neutralize helpers, caps via cap_fief_stats. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3E1E7:clear_fief_pair_6193:[HIGH] Zeroes the symmetric entries [a][b] and [b][a] in the 54-stride per-fief matrix at $6193 (adjacency/relations grid). Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3E21B:install_new_daimyo:[HIGH] Installs a new daimyo on a fief: fief_to_daimyo_map[fief] = list_op_6e4a(0xFF), province_ai_state=0, $6DA2=0, then confirm_prompt. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3E275:prompt_helper_e275:[LOW] Conditionally tests get_province_ai_state on $77A8 then confirm_prompt; exact purpose obscured. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3E2AF:copy_arms_record_5:[MED] Copies a 5-byte record from arg2 into $76A9 + arg1*5 (the per-fief arms/force record, stride 5). Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3E2D6:draw_daimyo_name_menu:[MED] Thin wrapper: ui_helper_d134(daimyo_name_table $77A8, $F77F) -- renders the daimyo-name list/menu. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3E425:find_fiefs_of_owner:[HIGH] Resolves arg1->daimyo (ui_helper_d772) then scans all fiefs collecting those with the same owner. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3E454:neutralize_fief:[MED] If province_ai_state != 0xFF: set state = -1, clear $6DA2, $6D2D = 20, copy_arms_record_5, recompute (find_record_9e3c). Depose/neutralize a fief. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3E4A2:build_owned_fief_list_6f89:[MED] Scans fiefs (filtered by get_6da2_cur), appends owned ones to the $6F89 list buffer, FF-terminated. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3E554:find_record_9e3c:[MED] If $6F5D<=8, SRAM-wrap reads the 34-byte record at $9E3C + $6F5D*34 and matches against arg1. 9 callers (hot). Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3E694:dispatch_map_helper_e694:[MED] Branches on scenario_fief_count==50, tail-calls map_helper_e5f2 with a $7FDD-indexed table byte. Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3E6B9:unpack_record_to_sram_e6b9:[MED] Unpacks $6EB1[$6F5B*2] via repeated div/mod into a 9-wide record, writes to SRAM $AEAC + idx*12 (uses ppu_upload_block_wrap/sram_wrap). Session C 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:0:bank0_entry:Bank 0 entry point. 3 bytes: JMP $A778. The 'rest of bank 0' is data — VM bytecode, sprite/tile data, and a few small native helpers callable from bytecode.
NesPrgRom:2778:vm_bootstrap:First instruction reached after RESET. JSR vm_entry ($E823) followed by inline VM bytecode that orchestrates the entire boot sequence (audio init, palette load, screen setup) and ultimately becomes the main game loop.
NesPrgRom:3:display_fullscreen_graphic_sequence:[MED AMENDED] ~530-byte multi-phase full-screen graphic/cinematic presenter: PPU blob uploads (ppu_upload_block_wrap) + 4 palette-fade loops + input-gated phase transitions + audio; ends two conditional message_display + infinite-hang JUMP. Proposer's cited calls were fabricated/mis-tiled; corrected from bytecode.
NesPrgRom:21E:verify_sram_save_integrity:[MED CONFIRMED] load-game gate: strcmp magic-string vs $7FED + running-sum checksum over $6001-$7FFF compared to stored $7FEB; match -> continue (ret 1), mismatch -> rewrite signature/flags + reformat prompt. Caller $89C9 (load path, $89A3).
NesPrgRom:377:transfer_arms_field_pct:[HIGH CONFIRMED] moves arg3% of source byte field (*arg2) into dest field (*arg1) via pct_op; caller $839A specializes it on the $76A9 per-fief arms record (stride 5).
NesPrgRom:5FC:prompt_roll_stat_value:[HIGH CONFIRMED] rolls a stat = rng_mod(50)+60 (60-109) with a roll/keep input loop; caller $8763 rolls the 5 daimyo stats.
NesPrgRom:62B:prompt_select_scenario_size:[HIGH CONFIRMED] 17-vs-50 fief scenario-size prompt; sets scenario_fief_count $6D9D = 17 or 50 + the map pointer, then SRAM init via syscall16_sram_wrap.
NesPrgRom:67F:display_prompt_message_b900:[MED CONFIRMED] message_display($B8F8) + ui_helper_d134(12,$B900) prompt wrapper; sole caller $86B3 (fief/scenario setup).
NesPrgRom:8AC:render_boot_title_screens:[MED AMENDED] boot/title two-screen opening (nametable+attr+tile blits, palette loops, press-A continue); reached only from vm_bootstrap via $89A3. NOT the Marry screen - cc35 is a generic screen enter/exit primitive (20 callers).
NesPrgRom:B70:select_msg_by_state_7b79:[HIGH CONFIRMED] 3-way state -> message-string selector over the byte at base+$7B79 (6->$BA28, 7->$BA31, else->$BA3A).
NesPrgRom:B9D:select_message_string_by_flags_and_arg:[MED AMENDED] picks a $BA-region message string by $6DA1 flag bits, then a 4-key switch on arg, default delegates to select_msg_by_state_7b79; feeds message_display.
NesPrgRom:BE6:find_first_enemy_owned_fief:[HIGH AMENDED] scans the FF-terminated owned-fief list ($6F89) and returns the first fief INDEX where is_enemy_owned; returns a province index, not an owner id.
NesPrgRom:C0E:is_selected_province_ai_state_5:[HIGH CONFIRMED] pure predicate: province_ai_state[$6CF7][selected_province_idx $6F5F] == 5.
NesPrgRom:C35:relations_matrix_cell_addr:[HIGH CONFIRMED] &relations[arg1][arg2] = arg1*54 + arg2 + $6193 (relations-matrix base, row stride 54; sibling of relations_matrix_get $8250).
NesPrgRom:DE1:dedup_owners_to_6f4f:[HIGH CONFIRMED] reads an FF-terminated fief list, dedups by owning daimyo (fief_to_daimyo_map via ui_helper_d772), writes the unique set to $6F4F (FF-terminated), returns the count.
NesPrgRom:E99:append_candidate_entry_6f67:[HIGH CONFIRMED] writes a 2-byte (value,flag) record at idx into the $6F67/$6F68 dual-lane list and rewrites the FF terminator; callers push flag 0 ($8FDB) / 1 ($961C).
NesPrgRom:EBC:compare_greater_with_coinflip_tiebreak:[HIGH CONFIRMED] returns (arg_a > arg_b) signed (SCMPLT); on equal returns a 50/50 rng_mod(2) coinflip.
NesPrgRom:FE0:stat_above_threshold_and_gap_predicate:[HIGH AMENDED] returns 1 iff (hi > 25) AND (hi - lo > 5); an absolute-threshold(25) + gap(5) test (not a truncation).
NesPrgRom:10C6:reset_byte_if_ge_100:[MED AMENDED] if *ptr >= 100 then *ptr = 0 (carry/wrap of a 0-99 stat, NOT a clamp-to-100); wrapper $90D7 = bump-then-wrap.
NesPrgRom:1154:check_daimyo_natural_death:[HIGH CONFIRMED] the VERIFIED natural-death formula: gated age>=70, triggers when (age-10-health/4) < rng_mod(300); returns weakness_flag[$6DD4]+1 on death, 2 if health==0. Caller $9194 runs the death-removal path.
NesPrgRom:11FD:clamp_value_to_range:[HIGH CONFIRMED] clamp arg2 to [arg1, arg3] (median-of-three); pure arithmetic.
NesPrgRom:1214:calc_year_scaled_random_value:[HIGH CONFIRMED] ((year $6D9F - 1560)/2 + 2)*10 + rng_mod(51); deterministic part grows +5/year, plus 0-50 noise.
NesPrgRom:122E:roll_small_or_large_random:[HIGH CONFIRMED] coinflip rng_mod(2) selects a small roll (5-10) vs a large roll (30-39); bimodal RNG helper.
NesPrgRom:39A:init_daimyo_arms_record:[HIGH AMENDED] makes FOUR transfer_arms_field_pct ($8377) calls over one daimyo arms record (idx*5+$76A9): two fixed 30% + two randomized rng_mod(20)+20 (20-39%) transfers of reserve fields +3/+4 into active +0/+1. Caller $858F inside the per-daimyo difficulty-scaling init loop $8507-$8593. Proposer undercounted (1 transfer); domain correct.
NesPrgRom:3E2:apply_scenario_starting_stat_boosts:[HIGH CONFIRMED] outer loop over scenario_fief_count: per non-AI fief, on a fief-id whitelist (50-fief {5,9,13,14,19,23,26,21,38,42,49,24} / 17-fief {1,2,4,7,10,15,16}) AND rng_mod(2), multiplies province record fields gold*2/men*4(or*3 17-fief)/+12*2/+18*2/+16*2; then pct-scales header(+24) by rng_mod(20)+80 for every fief. Scenario-init stat boosts. Opcode-exact.
NesPrgRom:694:prompt_select_player_daimyo:[HIGH CONFIRMED] setup-time daimyo-selection prompt (called per player slot from $8AB3): reads number_input, validates province_ai_state[$6CF7]==5 (available marker), displays chosen daimyo name ($77A8), commits by WRITING ai_state=5 + selected_province_idx $6F5F. Verifier corrected proposer/decompiler (gate is ==5 and commit writes 5, not 0).
NesPrgRom:763:daimyo_creation_stat_roll_screen:[HIGH AMENDED] full daimyo creation/edit screen ($8768-$88AB): palette/rect chrome, name draw ($77A8), field values ($7985), label loop over $F8AE; interactive climax = roll 6 stats into daimyo record (idx*7+$7530) via prompt_roll_stat_value ($85FC) with confirm/reroll-all (ui_helper_d3a7). Proposer name too narrow (just the roll).
NesPrgRom:9A3:init_new_game_state:[HIGH CONFIRMED] top-level new-game/scenario init: gated on verify_sram_save_integrity ($821E, bails via syscall on fail); fills $7FD5[0..8)=-1, $6F1B[i]=i per fief, zeroes $6CF7 province_ai_state over fiefs+4 daimyo slots, seeds $6E0B[i]=rng_mod(10)+8; drives scenario-size prompt + per-player init ($8694/$8763) + render_boot_title_screens. 18+ CALLs; call-index 0-edge artifact.
NesPrgRom:C1E:cur_flag_and_selected_ai_state5:[HIGH AMENDED] predicate: returns get_6da2_cur ($D9A9) AND is_selected_province_ai_state_5 ($8C0E) as 1/0. Verifier corrected proposer prose (true path returns 1 not 0 - decompiler drops the LOADL accumulator across labels). Caller $8C45 scans fiefs for cur-flag AND ai_state==5.
NesPrgRom:C45:set_6da1_bit7_if_no_ai_state5_province_found:[HIGH AMENDED] scans the $6F1A fief list for a province satisfying $8C1E (cur-flag AND ai_state==5); if NONE found, sets bit7 of $6DA1 via $D962. local11 is a found accumulator (not the stored flag). Verifier corrected INVERTED polarity (flag set on not-found, not on match).
NesPrgRom:C75:resolve_ownerless_province_succession:[MED AMENDED] picks who inherits a vacated province: if <2 candidates install_new_daimyo($6F63); else walk the $00FF-terminated candidate list at $6F4F, pick max province-value daimyo, install + mutate ai-state ($6CF7/$6DA2/$6E15) + name table $77A8. Sole caller $8E63. Proposer had the max-value mechanic; succession is the right frame.
NesPrgRom:E63:process_fiefs_with_state_ff:[MED AMENDED] loops all fiefs; for each ownerless one (province_state_is_FF $D999), builds the deduped owners list (dedup_owners_to_6F4F $8DE1) and calls resolve_ownerless_province_succession ($8C75). Action loop, NOT a finder (proposer mistook the trailing decompiler RETURN for a found-index).
NesPrgRom:ED3:display_two_message_prompt_then_compare:[MED AMENDED] selects two message strings ($DE78/$8B9D), renders a formatted two-message prompt + confirm (message_display + ui_helper_d134 x2 + confirm_prompt), then RETURNS compare_greater_with_coinflip_tiebreak ($8EBC) of two PASSED-IN args (slots 12/13), not the message values. Proposer conflated the displayed strings with the compared values.
NesPrgRom:F0A:ai_resolve_province_takeover_attempt:[MED AMENDED] contest on a target province: strength = sqrt(output+8)+sqrt(arms+14)+rng_mod(20)+10 vs defender field+16, decided by the $8ED3 UI contest. WIN ($8F51) -> conquer (install_new_daimyo/neutralize_fief + list ops); LOSS ($8F96) -> erode arms+16/output+8 by pct rng_mod(50)+10. Proposer only documented the loss branch.
NesPrgRom:FD3:append_candidate_zero_priority:[HIGH CONFIRMED] thin wrapper: append_candidate_entry_6f67 ($8E99) with priority/score field = 0. PUSH 0/13/12 -> CALL $8E99. No other logic.
NesPrgRom:FF8:collect_high_loyalty_provinces_to_candidate_list:[MED AMENDED] walks province-index list $7BAD; for AI-owned fiefs (via $8C1E) qualifies on field+12 LOYALTY (verifier corrected proposer +12=men): loyalty>25 AND (loyalty-arg1)>5, appending via $8FD3. Interactive (message/redraw/confirm) + applies a loyalty/wealth grow ($D940). Non-AI branch bumps +12 by rng_mod(30)+50.
NesPrgRom:10D7:saturating_sub_byte_then_reset_if_ge_100:[HIGH AMENDED] *ptr(local12) = max(0, *ptr - local13) via $CA12, THEN reset_byte_if_ge_100 ($90C6) clamps to 0 if >=100. NOT a thin wrapper (proposer missed the $CA12 saturating-sub the lossy C renders as ?). Called from the relations-matrix decay loops $90E8/$911E (decay-by-N across fief pairs).
NesPrgRom:10E8:normalize_relations_matrix_lower:[MED CONFIRMED] nested i/j loop bounded by scenario_fief_count, gated j>i (lower triangle): cell = relations_matrix_cell_addr ($8C35, arg1*54+arg2+$6193), apply $90D7 (bump-then-wrap-at-100). 4 callers in the AI turn region ($9F9C/$A06C/$A275/$A392). Per-cell op is bump+wrap not pure clamp (MED).
NesPrgRom:111E:normalize_relations_matrix_upper:[HIGH CONFIRMED] byte-identical to sibling $90E8 except the two index pushes are swapped (cell i*54+j vs j*54+i) = the transposed/other triangle of the stride-54 relations matrix at $6193. Gated i<j, apply $90D7 per cell.
NesPrgRom:1194:check_and_process_daimyo_natural_death:[HIGH AMENDED] per-daimyo (gated on $6DA2 active set): runs check_daimyo_natural_death ($9154, the verified (age-10-health/4)/300 age>=70 roll); on death removes from list ($DC0E/$DC3C), announces via name table $77A8 + death-type table $BBA5, clears fief pairs ($E1E7), reassigns territory (find_fiefs_of_owner $E425). Natural-death + succession handler. Called per-daimyo by an outer turn iterator.
NesPrgRom:124A:roll_period_rate_table_6e0b:[MED AMENDED] rolls a contiguous 5-word RNG rate array $6E0B-$6E13 (proven by the $8A34 i*2 read loop): rng/clamp/year-scaled/pct mixes. Caller $A495 runs it once per period (after period counter $6D9F INC, gated by mod-4 $6D5F). Dropped the unproven 'market' qualifier (no bytecode ties it to prices).
NesPrgRom:12A9:repay_province_debt_from_gold:[HIGH CONFIRMED] amt = min(debt@+2, gold@+0, cap arg2); gold -= amt; debt -= amt; early-return 1 if no debt. Field +0=gold/+2=debt match live $7001 record (loan/debt mechanic). Caller $A2C5 sweeps every fief paying down debt (with cap_fief_stats $D836).
NesPrgRom:12D9:deduct_b_from_a_void_b_if_overdrawn:[MED AMENDED] *A(local12) -= *B(local13); if *A<=0 going in OR *A<0 after, zeroes *B (the source/charge), leaving *A negative. Verifier REFUTED the 'clamp_negative' framing (A is never clamped; B gets voided on overdraft). Leaf, no host_calls.
NesPrgRom:12F9:random_ravage_province_field:[HIGH CONFIRMED] generic probabilistic field reducer: 50% no-op (rng_mod 2), else *field = pct_op(rng_mod(30)+40, *field) (40-69% of original), returns 1/0. Built into the defending-province ravage sweep: 6 field wrappers ($9323..$93AA over $6F63 record) + orchestrator $93BF. Decompiler C lossy here; bytecode authoritative.
NesPrgRom:1323:ravage_defender_field_off10:[HIGH CONFIRMED] wrapper: random_ravage_province_field on battle_defending_province ($6F63) record field +10 ($700B). 1st call in the $93BF ravage sweep.
NesPrgRom:1338:ravage_defender_output_and_bump_selected_arms:[HIGH CONFIRMED] ravages defender output@+8 ($7009); on a fire, also adds rng_mod(100)+100 to the ATTACKER (selected_province_idx) arms@+14 ($700F). The plunder-transfer member of the $93BF sweep.
NesPrgRom:136B:ravage_defender_field_off4:[HIGH CONFIRMED] wrapper: random_ravage_province_field on defender ($6F63) field +4 ($7005). 2nd call in the $93BF sweep.
NesPrgRom:1380:ravage_defender_arms:[HIGH CONFIRMED] wrapper: random_ravage_province_field on defender ($6F63) arms@+14 ($700F). Member of the $93BF sweep.
NesPrgRom:1395:ravage_defender_field_off18:[HIGH CONFIRMED] wrapper: random_ravage_province_field on defender ($6F63) field +18 ($7013). Member of the $93BF sweep.
NesPrgRom:13AA:ravage_defender_loyalty:[HIGH CONFIRMED] wrapper: random_ravage_province_field on defender ($6F63) loyalty@+12 ($700D). Member of the $93BF sweep.
NesPrgRom:13BF:ravage_defending_province_sweep:[HIGH CONFIRMED] post-combat pillage: opens UI over the loser (message/daimyo-name/confirm), then calls the 6 single-field ravage wrappers ($9323/$936B/$93AA/$9395/$9380/$9338, offsets +10/+4/+12/+18/+14/+8) in sequence, early-out on first fire; fallthrough harsher-ravages field+10 (rng_mod(30)+60) or scribbles the daimyo record if already razed. Sole caller driver_war.
NesPrgRom:146D:get_daimyo_stat4_by_fief:[HIGH CONFIRMED] leaf: returns *(byte*)(fief_to_daimyo_record_addr(arg1)+4) = field +4 of the owning daimyo 7-byte record ($752F stride-7). Field +4 = CHARISMA (per daimyo field map); kept generic stat4 here, $947A names it charisma in context.
NesPrgRom:147A:avg_daimyo_charisma_over_fief_list:[HIGH AMENDED] populates the $00FF-terminated $6F89 list (marry_helper $E4DC), then averages get_daimyo_stat4_by_fief (=owner CHARISMA@+4) over it = sum/count. The marriage subsystem averaging owner charisma across candidate fiefs. Proposer's generic stat4 -> charisma.
NesPrgRom:14B1:announce_provinces_by_ai_state_mode:[MED AMENDED] mode arg (1/2/default) selects a header string, then walks the $00FF-terminated province list at $7BAD, and for each province with nonzero ai_state shows a per-province daimyo-name confirm prompt. Display/report loop, NOT an accumulator (proposer's 'scan/accumulate' refuted - no acc).
NesPrgRom:152F:avg_byte_array_6d2d_over_fiefs:[HIGH CONFIRMED] arithmetic mean of the per-fief byte array based at $6D2D over fiefs 0..scenario_fief_count-1 (sum/count). No host_calls.
NesPrgRom:1558:avg_province_wealth_over_fiefs:[HIGH AMENDED] split-mean (UDIV+UMOD) of province field +14 ($700F) over all fiefs = floor(sum/count). Field +14 = WEALTH (proposer said arms; 3 field-map sources - dashboard.lua/sram-decode-province.py/vm_decompile.py - agree +14=wealth, +22=arms).
NesPrgRom:1595:province_conquest_roll_predicate:[MED AMENDED] displays + computes a weighted random score from province field+18, field+16, and random daimyo charisma(+4) terms; returns TRUE when 2*score < field+16 (via SCMPLT, coinflip on tie). Single caller $97B2 gates daimyo-elimination/conquest on TRUE. Proposer mechanism right; 'below_threshold' imprecise (test is 2*score<field16).
NesPrgRom:1614:append_candidate_priority1:[HIGH CONFIRMED] priority-1 counterpart of $8FD3: append_candidate_entry_6f67 ($8E99) with the priority/flag field = 1 (vs 0). Thin wrapper.
NesPrgRom:1621:reassign_daimyo24_fiefs_to_owner50:[MED AMENDED] loops fiefs; for each owned by daimyo 24 with $6DA2 flag clear, sets fief_to_daimyo_map ($6E15) = 50 + refreshes via find_record_9e3c ($E554); then zeroes province_ai_state[selected], sets $6DA1 bit, UI. Byte-symmetric mirror of $99AB (owner 50->24). A scripted 50-fief reassignment event; literal owner-IDs (proposer's 'zealot' unsupported by bytecode).
NesPrgRom:16B0:scenario50_fief30_event_eligible:[MED AMENDED] eligibility predicate for a scripted 50-fief event: hard-gates scenario_fief_count==50 AND fief==30 AND owner==24 AND daimyo-record(30) >= 40 (proposer had <=40, direction inverted) AND flags clear; then a combat-strength accumulation ($6F81 vs $270F cap) + RNG roll; on full pass triggers $9621 + sets $6E48=1, returns 1. 'zealot/uprising' semantics dropped (no bytecode support).
NesPrgRom:1778:revolt_spread_sweep_flip_fief_ownership:[MED AMENDED] walks the $00FF-terminated $7BAD fief list; per fief: $96B0 true aborts the sweep; $8C1E true counts/collects via $9614; else $9595 spread predicate -> on TRUE flips fief ownership + install_new_daimyo ($E21B) + zero ai_state (defection), on FALSE grows field+18 / decays field+16 (rebellion-pressure meter). Confirmed ownership-flip; 'zealot' dropped (no religion marker, message-string IDs undecodable here).
NesPrgRom:1879:mark_6f89_list_entry_by_value:[HIGH AMENDED] scans the fixed $00FF-terminated global list at $6F89 for an entry == arg; on match writes 0xC8 (-56, the 'marked' sentinel) and returns found. Proposer mechanics right; list is the fixed $6F89 global, not an arbitrary ptr (cross-ref $98C6/$9974 use the same 0xC8 sentinel).
NesPrgRom:18A3:set_fief_ownership_record:[HIGH CONFIRMED] canonical parameterized fief-ownership writer: by index arg, stores fief_to_daimyo_map[$6E15]=owner, $6DA2[]=flag, province_ai_state[$6CF7]=ai_state, then find_record_9e3c ($E554) to recompute. Real callers $9963/$9996 (grep; call-index misses CALL_abs_imm1). Sibling idiom of install_new_daimyo/neutralize_fief/reassign_fiefs_to_conqueror.
NesPrgRom:18C6:select_provinces_and_assign_ai_state:[MED AMENDED] 3 phases: walk $6F4F candidate list into a stack buffer (marking matched $6F89 entries 0xC8 via $9879); append more from arg2's list; then for each buffered entry COMMIT via set_fief_ownership_record ($98A3) with ai_state preserved + role constant 51. Proposer captured only the list-build phases, missed the consequential state-mutation phase 3.
NesPrgRom:1974:process_first_n_unmarked_list_entries:[MED AMENDED] iterate the byte-list (cursor arg) for N (arg) entries: stop on $00FF, skip 0xC8-marked; for each unmarked entry CALL set_fief_ownership_record ($98A3) THEN mark it 0xC8 + decrement remaining. The $98A3 record-processing is the work; 0xC8 is a 'done' marker (proposer's 'mark' undersold it).
NesPrgRom:19AB:reassign_owner50_fiefs_to_daimyo24:[MED CONFIRMED] byte-symmetric mirror of $9621: loops fiefs, where owner==50 sets fief_to_daimyo_map ($6E15)=24 + find_record_9e3c ($E554); two-path event handler (Path B sets selected=+30, runs $98C6/$9974, sweeps $7FD5 24->51). Verifier corrected: ai_state set to 5 not 0 (decompiler mis-renders the qimm).
NesPrgRom:1AAC:driver_diplomacy_gold_transfer:[HIGH CONFIRMED] diplomacy effect: gated on diplomacy_helper ($E3A4) + confirm; inputs amount, then selected-province gold@+0 += amount and battle_defending_province gold@+0 -= amount (gold moves target->self). Sibling of the marry variant $9B7F. Caller $9B55 in $9B12.
NesPrgRom:1B12:ai_scan_idle_fiefs_run_diplomacy_action:[MED AMENDED] scans fiefs (flag $6DA2 set AND ai_state==0 idle), builds a candidate list via combat_helper_dad7 ($DAD7), and on the first eligible target DISPATCHES the diplomacy action $9AAC (not just a finder, per proposer). Sequential-scan twin of the random-pick $9BE5.
NesPrgRom:1B7F:marry_transfer_gold_between_provinces:[HIGH AMENDED] marriage gold transfer: gated on marry_helper_e315 ($E315); selected-province gold@+0 += amt, battle_defending_province gold@+0 -= amt (target->self). Byte-mirror of diplomacy $9AAC. Leaf effect inside the marriage loop (caller $9BE5), NOT a driver (the Marry driver is $9DC4); dropped the driver_ prefix.
NesPrgRom:1BE5:ai_event_marry_random_eligible_fief:[MED AMENDED] picks a random fief (rng_mod scenario_fief_count), skips ai-state-set or rest-blocked fiefs, sets it as battle_defending_province and INVOKES the marriage action $9B7F on the first eligible candidate. Random-pick variant of $9B12. Reached from $9C84 switch branch 0.
NesPrgRom:1C22:random_ravage_sweep_bounded_fiefs:[MED AMENDED] 50%-gated sweep over fiefs (rng_mod(20)<3 ~15% per fief, skip ai-state-set, action count bounded by 8-$6E09): on a hit swaps selected<->defending and runs ravage_defending_province_sweep ($93BF). Loop bound is $6D9D not $6E09 (proposer wrong). $9C84 switch default branch.
NesPrgRom:1C84:random_event_type_dispatch:[HIGH CONFIRMED] 50%-gated (rng_mod 2) random-event selector: rng_mod(4) switch dispatching one of three event handlers ($9BE5 marriage / $9B12 diplomacy / $9C22 ravage), each a distinct CALL+RETURN. Verifier REFUTED the lossy-C 'all converge to $9BE5' artifact (coincident JUMP targets hid the other two CALLs). Pure dispatcher.
NesPrgRom:1CB3:decay_fief_list_wealth_and_output_disaster1:[HIGH AMENDED] AI disaster effect handler #1: over the $7BAD fief list, wealth@+14 -= rng_mod(4)+1 and output@+8 = pct_op(pct_op(90, +10 header), output). Planner-selected (pointer loaded at $A4DA in the $A4AB planner, type 1 of 3 vs $9D00/$9ED9). Proposer's mechanics right; 'sabotage' too specific -> disaster type 1.
NesPrgRom:1D00:random_event_ravage_output_hidden_mark_weakness:[MED AMENDED] disaster effect handler #2 (msg #31): over the $7BAD list, hidden field+16 and output+8 each scaled to 50-99% (pct_op rng_mod(50)+50); conditionally writes daimyo_weakness_flag $6DD4[owner] from a daimyo-record byte vs 50, plus a byte_helper_ca12 side-write. Planner-selected (pointer at $A4F0). Proposer missed the $6DD4 weakness write.
NesPrgRom:1D86:square_over_2025_probability_roll:[HIGH CONFIRMED] clamps arg1<=50, returns (arg1*arg1) < rng_mod(2025) = the verified event-spawn probability x^2/2025 capped at 50 (rediscovered blind from bytecode; matches event_spawn_formula memory). Pure predicate. Used by $9DA3/$9E21 as per-stat eligibility rolls.
NesPrgRom:1DA3:ai_event_eligibility_check_loyalty_variant:[HIGH CONFIRMED] per-fief event-eligibility predicate: three $9D86 (x^2/2025) rolls on loyalty@+12 ($700D), (100 - $6D2D[fief]), and daimyo charisma@+4; any TRUE -> gate block (output>0, +16>2, !tax_helper_db12, !state_FF, rng_mod(4)==0) -> return 1. Loyalty variant; sibling $9E21 keys on +18. Dispatched by $9E7C (arg1==1).
NesPrgRom:1E21:ai_event_eligibility_check_field18_variant:[MED AMENDED] sibling of $9DA3: $9D86 rolls on hidden field+18 ($7013) + charisma@+4, tax_helper_db12-selected rng bound, +16>2, !state_FF -> 0/1. Verifier REFUTED 'wealth' (no +14 access; keys on the +18 hidden field). Dispatched by $9E7C (arg1!=1).
NesPrgRom:1E7C:select_event_eligibility_check_by_type:[HIGH CONFIRMED] dispatcher: returns 0 if province_state_is_FF; else arg1==1 -> $9DA3 (loyalty variant) else $9E21 (+18 variant). Caller $9E9D sweeps fiefs calling this per-fief.
NesPrgRom:1E9D:build_event_eligible_fief_candidate_list:[HIGH CONFIRMED] scans all scenario fiefs (source list $6F1B), filters by per-type eligibility ($9E7C), appends survivors to the $00FF-terminated candidate list at $7BAD, returns any-found flag. Caller $9ED9 (event-handler driver). Proposer swapped the in/out list bases (corrected).
NesPrgRom:1ED9:ai_event_build_two_batches_dispatch_or_announce:[HIGH AMENDED] disaster/event handler type-3 (pointer-selected at $A4FA in the planner): builds 2 eligible-fief batches ($9E9D for both event types); if BOTH eligible -> random_event_type_dispatch ($9C84); else FALLBACK switch fires a UI-announced event ($8FF8 loyalty-grow or $9778 revolt). Sibling of $9CB3/$9D00.
NesPrgRom:1F57:event_boost_province_wealth_loyalty:[HIGH CONFIRMED] 50%-gated positive event: arg2-province WEALTH@+14 += rng_mod(10)+charisma/10, LOYALTY@+12 += rng_mod(40)+charisma/10 (charisma via get_daimyo_stat4_by_fief). Per-turn sweep caller $9FE5 in $9F8C. Sibling of the gold/output variant $A128.
NesPrgRom:1F8C:per_turn_age_daimyo_decay_health_and_province_stats:[HIGH AMENDED] per-period driver (turn-dispatch case0 from $A30D switch): normalizes relations matrix, then per daimyo record AGE@+0 ++ and HEALTH@+1 -- (7-byte stride; fields per verified $9154 natural-death), then per AI-province decays loyalty@+12/wealth@+14/hidden@+16. Proposer's 'decrement_debt' REFUTED (it's health+stat decay, no debt touched).
NesPrgRom:2066:init_province_highwater_from_records:[HIGH CONFIRMED] per fief, copies 4 words from province record +8/+10/+12/+14 (output/dams/loyalty/wealth) into the stride-8 fief_history_table ($6003). Plain snapshot/init; sibling $A0A9 does the max-UPDATE. The documented high-water-mark mechanic.
NesPrgRom:20A9:update_province_highwater_marks:[HIGH CONFIRMED] monotonic high-water update: for province fields +8/+10/+12/+14, if field >= stored table value ($6003/$6005/$6007/$6009 stride-8) store field. Pure leaf, paired with the $A066 initializer.
NesPrgRom:2128:event_boost_province_gold_output:[HIGH CONFIRMED] positive event: arg2-province GOLD@+0 += rng_mod(10)+charisma/10 unconditionally, then 50%-gated OUTPUT@+8 += same. Caller $A295 in $A26F, only for non-owned provinces. Gold/output sibling of the wealth/loyalty variant $9F57.
NesPrgRom:215B:consume_province_army_upkeep:[HIGH AMENDED] army upkeep: drains MEN@+16 /2 from BOTH gold@+0 and rice@+6; if min(rice,gold) < men/2, starves the army down to 2*available (men = avail<<1). The '-MEN/2' term of the harvest formula. Drains gold too, not just rice (proposer's 'food' -> 'upkeep').
NesPrgRom:2191:calc_charisma_scaled_income_variance:[HIGH CONFIRMED] returns pct_op(input, charisma/2) = the half-charisma-scaled RNG spread bound for harvest income variance. charisma via get_daimyo_stat4_by_fief(+4). Called by $A1E2 (gold) and $A21F (rice) as the rng_mod range.
NesPrgRom:21AA:calc_fief_harvest_base_term:[HIGH AMENDED] base yield term = pct_op(mult_6D2D, hiwater_6009) + pct_op(mult_6D2D, pct_op(40, hiwater_6007)); no men-sub, no RNG (those live in callers $A1E2/$A21F). The '$A1AA' base term of the cracked harvest formula; feeds both gold and rice.
NesPrgRom:21E2:calc_fief_gold_income:[HIGH CONFIRMED] gold harvest term: calc_fief_harvest_base_term ($A1AA) + town-pct + rng_mod(charisma-variance $A191), clamped to header@+24 (dev ceiling). Result added to gold@+0 by the $A26F sweep. Town/dev high-water pair $6007/$6009.
NesPrgRom:221F:calc_fief_rice_income:[HIGH CONFIRMED] rice harvest term: same shape as $A1E2 but reads the OUTPUT high-water pair $6003/$6005; base + 2 rng_mod terms, clamped to header@+24. Result added to rice@+6 by the $A26F sweep. (Note: live map has rice@+6, men@+16 — not the ROM-defaults shorthand.)
NesPrgRom:226F:harvest_income_sweep_all_fiefs:[HIGH CONFIRMED] the per-turn harvest driver: loops all fiefs, gates on ai_state + loyalty@+12 != 0, adds calc_fief_gold_income ($A1E2) to gold@+0 and calc_fief_rice_income ($A21F) to rice@+6, then per fief repay_province_debt_from_gold ($92A9) + consume_province_army_upkeep ($A15B) + cap_fief_stats ($D836). The cracked harvest formula, as named code.
NesPrgRom:22DF:roll_3pct_event_chance:[HIGH CONFIRMED] 4-instruction predicate: returns rng_mod(100) < 3 = fixed 3% probability. No records touched. Event-gate used by the planner's candidate-list build.
NesPrgRom:22ED:drift_daimyo_stat3_random:[HIGH CONFIRMED] daimyo record byte +3 perturbed by -5..+5: *ptr += rng_mod(11); *ptr -= 5 (ptr = daimyo_record_addr(idx)+3). Per-turn stat drift, called in the $A30D loop. ($752F 7-byte record: age@+1, charisma@+4.)
NesPrgRom:230D:per_period_fief_daimyo_update_driver:[MED AMENDED] multi-stage per-period driver: loop1 per fief calls drift_daimyo_stat3_random ($A2ED) + (if $6D2D<88) decays loyalty@+12 to 90%; then UI + process_fiefs_with_state_ff ($8E63); then a $6D5F (period mod-4) switch dispatching $9F8C/$A066/$A26F/$90E8; loop2 per fief check_and_process_daimyo_natural_death ($9194). Proposer wrongly called the switch handlers 'no-op' (lossy C) and named only the loyalty branch.
NesPrgRom:23AA:write_sram_save_checksum_and_signature:[HIGH AMENDED] the WRITE/STAMP side of save integrity: accumulates the syscall-22 checksum over SRAM and STORES it to $7FEB, strcpy's the signature to $7FED, then UI. Sibling of verify_sram_save_integrity ($821E) which READS+compares the same. Proposer's 'compute checksum' missed the store.
NesPrgRom:2455:ai_strategic_turn_planner:[HIGH CONFIRMED] THE AI per-turn driver root (JMP'd from vm_bootstrap): clears daimyo_weakness_flag, gates on $6DA1 bit7, advances period ($6D5F/$6D9F + roll_period_rate_table $924A + sub-driver $A30D), pointer-selects a disaster/event handler ($9CB3/$9D00/$9ED9), builds the event candidate list, then the WAR-TARGET loop at $A581: daimyo_weakness_flag[i] = (rng_mod(400) < (100-health)) | flag = the (100-health)/400 weakest-enemy weighting (matches ai_war_architecture), gated by war_helper_d972 + $8C1E, with daimyo-name war-declaration UI.
NesPrgRom:25D5:rng_mod_30:[HIGH AMENDED] returns rng_mod((const_two+1)*10) = rng_mod(30) = 0..29. Pure RNG tail-call helper (proposer's '0_to_30' was off-by-one; rng_mod(n) is 0..n-1). Used by $A5E6.
NesPrgRom:25E6:spawn_zealot_uprising_force_from_province:[MED AMENDED] populates the Ikko-Ikki zealot uprising attacker slot (idx 50 / record $7515) by scaling the target province's record (8 pct_op entries = 40-59% of defender stats) while depleting its output@+8/hidden@+16/men@+6; charisma-gated transfers; sets selected_province_idx=50. PRE-battle setup (scratch $6F7D-$6F81 consumed later by apply_conquest_outcome), NOT post-conquest reinit. Sole caller vm_bootstrap $A7E5.
NesPrgRom:2742:shuffle_fief_turn_order_array:[HIGH AMENDED] Fisher-Yates shuffle of the turn-order byte array at $6F1B (identity-init'd by init_new_game_state): per fief, cap_fief_stats ($D836) + two rng_mod($6D9D) draws + swap_byte ($CB80). The documented per-turn turn-order randomization. Caller vm_bootstrap $A803 (once per turn). Proposer's 'no-ops' REFUTED (host_calls hidden by lossy C).
NesPrgRom:3C54F:nmi_off:Clear bit 7 of ppuctrl_shadow (disable NMI generation); used as the NMI re-entry guard
NesPrgRom:3C567:rendering_on:OR $18 into ppumask_shadow (enable BG + sprite rendering)
NesPrgRom:3C570:write_ppumask:Write A to PPUMASK ($2001) and update ppumask_shadow
NesPrgRom:3C68A:nmi_on:Set bit 7 of ppuctrl_shadow (enable NMI generation)
NesPrgRom:3C693:ppu_safe_gate:Composite preamble for foreground PPU updates: nmi_off → wait_vblank → rendering_off
NesPrgRom:3C69D:rendering_off:AND $E7 into ppumask_shadow (clear BG + sprite enable; blank screen)
NesPrgRom:3C6A6:write_ppuctrl:Write A to PPUCTRL ($2000) and update ppuctrl_shadow
NesPrgRom:3C537:wait_vblank:Spin until PPUSTATUS bit 7 set; early-out if skip_vblank_wait ($0080) non-zero. Calls music_driver during spin.
NesPrgRom:3C628:controller_poll:Strobe $4016 and shift 8 bits into $006E (P1) or $006F (P2); X = player index
NesPrgRom:3C6AD:mul_xy_by_3:Helper used by BRK dispatcher: multiply X register by 3 with carry, used to scale task ID to table offset
NesPrgRom:3C6D4:palette_upload:If palette_dirty != 0: blank screen, set PPUADDR=$3F00, copy 32 bytes from palette_shadow to PPUDATA, restore rendering, clear palette_dirty
NesPrgRom:3C7A5:music_driver:NMI music tick. Calls trigger pass at $C7AC, then sequencer pass at $C817, then RTS. (Disasm6 misread this region as a data table.)
NesPrgRom:3C7AC:music_trigger_pass:Pass 1: scan 5 voices at $0734; for any voice with byte 0 in 1..4, write 4 APU register bytes and set byte 0 = byte 0 + 4 (one-shot)
NesPrgRom:3C7DE:music_voice_check:Per-voice trigger check: skip if byte 0 is 0 (idle) or >= 5 (dormant), else call music_voice_play
NesPrgRom:3C7EF:music_voice_play:Per-voice play: compute APU base from byte 0, optionally skip if triangle mute, write bytes 1-4 to APU registers
NesPrgRom:3C817:music_sequencer_pass:Pass 2: for each active voice, decrement byte 8 (duration countdown). When zero, advance song pointer (bytes 6-7), load new pitch (bytes 3-4), trigger (byte 0), reset countdown (byte 8).
NesPrgRom:3C7C9:music_advance_voice:music_ptr += 9 (advance to next 9-byte voice record); music_voice_idx++. The scan-step shared by trigger_pass and sequencer_pass.
NesPrgRom:3C83D:music_voice_step:Per-voice sequencer tick (called from music_sequencer_pass for active voices). If stream byte < 5: load note (music_load_note). Else: countdown record[8] via music_dec_duration; on expiry, music_next_event drives the next stream event.
NesPrgRom:3C857:music_load_note:Start a note: music_load_voice_cfg then write 4 note-parameter bytes (from the stream) into record offsets [0,1,2,4] via music_read_stream_byte.
NesPrgRom:3C877:music_load_voice_cfg:Copy the voice's 3-byte instrument config from v0_config[voice_idx*3] ($0725) into record offsets [5,6,7] (bank + stream pointer).
NesPrgRom:3C894:music_read_stream_byte:Banked song-stream fetch: save current bank, switch to record[5] (song bank), read one byte via the record[6,7] pointer, increment that pointer (record[6,7]), restore bank. Returns byte in A. The cross-bank stream reader the whole driver runs on.
NesPrgRom:3C8C4:music_dec_duration:Decrement record[8] (note-duration countdown) and store back. Returns Z when it hits zero (time for next event).
NesPrgRom:3C8CE:music_next_event:Process one stream event: music_read_stream_byte; if < $F0 it's a note -> music_set_pitch + music_set_duration; if >= $F0 it's a command -> music_handle_command. Loops until a playable event is set.
NesPrgRom:3C8E4:music_handle_command:Stream control byte >= $F0. $F0 = note-off (silence the APU channel for this voice, clear its active flag, return C set = stop). Other values fall through to music_restart_stream (pattern loop/restart).
NesPrgRom:3C906:music_restart_stream:Reload the 3-byte voice config into record[5,6,7] and clear record[0] — i.e. restart the voice's pattern stream from its configured start (the loop command target). jmp-reached from music_handle_command.
NesPrgRom:3C929:music_set_pitch:Convert note -> APU timer period via music_note_to_period, then splice the period hi/lo into record[3,4] (the channel's timer bytes), preserving the low control bits of record[4].
NesPrgRom:3C94B:music_note_to_period:Note byte -> 16-bit APU period in $7E/$7F: low nibble indexes the 12-entry base-period table tab_c96f (2 bytes each); high nibble is the octave (right-shift the period that many times).
NesPrgRom:3C990:music_set_duration:Read the next stream byte (note length), shift left 3 (x8 = ticks), store into record[8] (the duration countdown).
NesPrgRom:3C757:reset_ppu_init:Reset-path PPU init: ppu_safe_gate, then upload $30 bytes from tab_c775 to PPU $0000, then screen_on. Walked 2026-05-31; was the pre-identified b15_c757.
NesPrgRom:3CBCD:sqrt_int:Integer square root (native code; chapter 9). Classic restoring algorithm, 2 bits per iteration, 8 iterations over 16-bit input. Called as host_call sqrt_int, $02 with one word arg on the data stack. Used by Grow/Dam/Build/Train effects to drive the diminishing-returns curve.
NesPrgRom:3D70D:pct_op:Percentage operator (bytecode sub; this session fully decoded). Computes base * pct / 100 with integer truncation, split-by-10 so no intermediate product exceeds 16 bits. Args: arg1=base, arg2=pct. Fast path: if pct==100 return base. Otherwise return (base/10)*(pct/10) + (base%10)*pct/100 + (pct%10)*(base/10)/10. Used by all redistribution tails (Grow drains loyalty+dams, Build drains wealth, Tax response, etc.).
NesPrgRom:3D6B8:math32_3arg:CONFIRMED 2026-05-25: 3-arg math helper computing (arg1 × arg2) / arg3 in 32-bit signed arithmetic. Uses ext-opcodes: $25 sign-extend 16→32, $14 push regA 32-bit, $15 pop into regB, $01 unsigned multiply, $02 signed divide, $27 RTS. Returns -1 if arg3==0. CRITICAL CAVEAT for Grow: callers push only 2 args explicitly (sqrt + neg-const_two); arg3 reads uninitialized stack memory at caller's frame[-4]. Runtime value of arg3 determined by execution history of the caller, not by an explicit push.
NesPrgRom:3D6DE:math32_2arg:2-arg extended-opcode math helper (bytecode sub). Returns 0 if both args are 0. Similar B7-prefix shape to math32_3arg but with ext_op $19 (a different multiply/scale primitive). Called by Grow/Build for a refinement step. EXACT formula pending ext-opcode decode.
NesPrgRom:3D326:message_display:Display a message string. Called by 30 distinct command drivers — the most-used helper in the lord-command menu. Args: typically a 16-bit string pointer pushed before the call. The 'show feedback prompt' primitive.
NesPrgRom:3D766:confirm_prompt:Show a confirmation prompt (likely 'OK?' / yes-no). Called by 22 drivers. Common tail of any command that has a destructive or committal step.
NesPrgRom:3CEC4:redraw_window:Redraw a screen region / window. Called by 17 drivers. The 'restore display after my prompts' primitive.
NesPrgRom:3D5E9:number_input:Number-input prompt with cap. Called by 15 drivers (Tax rate, Grow amount, Send rice/gold, etc.). Args appear to include the maximum allowed value — Chapter 9 noted the Grow input is capped at the province's gold.
NesPrgRom:3CC89:ui_helper_cc89:UI helper called by 14 drivers. Specific role TBD — appears in command pre-roll/post-roll. Candidate: cursor-restore or selection-reset.
NesPrgRom:3D134:ui_helper_d134:Helper called by 13 drivers. Often follows message_display. Candidate: format-and-print (the '%d' / '%s' substitution layer).
NesPrgRom:3D3A7:ui_helper_d3a7:Helper called by 8 drivers. TBD.
NesPrgRom:3E80C:ui_helper_e80c:Helper called by 15 drivers. TBD.
NesPrgRom:3CC7B:ui_helper_cc7b:Helper called by 6 drivers. TBD.
NesPrgRom:3D7EA:ui_helper_d7ea:Helper called by 5 drivers. TBD.
NesPrgRom:3E510:ui_helper_e510:Helper called by 5 drivers (Send, Pact, View, Marry — the 'select target province from a list' command set). Candidate: cursor/menu enter primitive.
NesPrgRom:3D77E:ui_helper_d77e:Helper called by 5 drivers (Marry, Pact among them). TBD.
NesPrgRom:3CB5E:min_word:Tiny 11-instruction function: min(arg1, arg2) as signed words. Returns smaller of the two via cmp_slt + branch. The cap mechanism behind 'morale caps at koku', 'dams cap at 100', etc. Heavily used by the field-cap-sweep at $D836 and by command-post-cleanups (Build, Grow, etc. — anywhere a stat needs to be clamped to a ceiling).
NesPrgRom:3D351:ui_helper_d351:Helper called by 4 drivers (Hire — chapter 11 notes the Men/Ninja type prompt routes through this). Candidate: 2-choice prompt.
NesPrgRom:3CD20:ui_helper_cd20:Helper called by 3 drivers. TBD.
NesPrgRom:3CA52:rng_mod:rng_next() mod arg1. 6-instruction bytecode wrapper: bails with 0 if arg1<1, else calls rng_next_wrapper ($CA46), then mod_signed by arg1. Returns 0..arg1-1 if rng is positive. Used by Train (X=ca52(20) for skill gain, Y=ca52(10) for Luck/IQ bonus check), and likely Marry too.
NesPrgRom:3CA46:rng_next_wrapper:3-instruction wrapper around syscall #17 (syscall_rng_next at $C1C3). Pushes 17 via op_8D_sbyte, fires syscall_dispatch, returns the 16-bit pseudo-random value. The bytecode-accessible entry point to the game's RNG.
NesPrgRom:3DAD7:combat_helper_dad7:Helper called by Move + War. Combat/military pre-roll.
NesPrgRom:3DD3A:combat_helper_dd3a:Helper called by Move + War. Combat/military pre-roll.
NesPrgRom:3D972:war_helper_d972:Helper called only by War. Combat-prep. = daimyo_weakness_flag[fief_to_daimyo_map[arg1]] (reads the weakness/condition mark of a province's owner).
NesPrgRom:3D59D:select_province_by_cursor:Returns the cursor-selected fief index (1..fief_count) for province_select_prompt: walks via sub_D3ED, bounds by arg1=scenario_fief_count. The selection PICK — same machinery for player AND AI (no separate AI scorer).
NesPrgRom:3D3ED:cursor_nav_loop:Menu/cursor navigation loop: switch(sub_D14E()) on NES button bits (1=R,2=L,16=Start,32=Sel,64=B,128=A) to move the selection cursor over candidates. The war-target PICK bottoms out HERE — controller input, not a target-scorer (read 2026-05-31). AI drives the same path via sub_D14E's AI branch.
NesPrgRom:3D9B7:is_enemy_owned:Candidate target predicate: returns (fief_to_daimyo_map[ui_helper_d77e()] == arg) — i.e. the candidate fief's owner matches the target daimyo (enemy-ownership match). Eligibility, not strength. Read 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3D999:province_state_is_FF:Returns ($6CF7[arg1] == 0xFF) — province is in the EXCLUDED state. Eligibility filter used by combat_helper_dd3a. Read 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3CBBD:syscall16_sram_wrap:Thin wrapper around syscall 16 (sram_block_checksum/copy). Called by combat_helper_dd3a after filtering the candidate list — plumbing, not scoring. Read 2026-05-31.
NesPrgRom:3E3A4:diplomacy_helper:Diplomacy subsystem helper. Called by Pact (chapter 11).
NesPrgRom:3DA4F:diplomacy_helper2:Second diplomacy subsystem helper called by Pact.
NesPrgRom:3DA7D:diplomacy_helper3:Diplomacy helper called by Marry.
NesPrgRom:3E4DC:marry_helper_e4dc:Marry-specific helper.
NesPrgRom:3E315:marry_helper_e315:Marry-specific helper.
NesPrgRom:3E76F:marry_helper_e76f:Marry-specific helper.
NesPrgRom:3CC35:marry_helper_cc35:Marry-specific helper.
NesPrgRom:3CC69:trade_helper_cc69:Trade-specific helper.
NesPrgRom:3DB35:ui_helper_db35:Sub-handler helper.
NesPrgRom:3DB12:tax_helper_db12:Tax-specific helper.
NesPrgRom:3D759:ui_helper_d759:Helper called by 3 drivers.
NesPrgRom:3D772:ui_helper_d772:Helper called by 2 drivers.
NesPrgRom:3E5F2:map_helper_e5f2:Map-rendering helper called by Map (chapter 11).
NesPrgRom:3C4DC:ui_unused:Reserved.
NesPrgRom:79B2:command_driver_table:34-entry pointer table — entry N points to the bytecode subroutine that drives menu command N+1. Entries 0-20 are the 21 lord commands, 21-33 are sub-handlers reachable from within those drivers. See command-table.txt for the full listing. Chapter 9's foundational find.
NesPrgRom:56D1:driver_move:Command 1 (Move) driver. Relocate troops between own provinces. Calls effect_move ($8CA5) after capacity-check, dest-pick, count-input, lead-personally prompt. Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:5850:driver_war:Command 2 (War) driver. Launch an attack. Heaviest single driver (154 insns, 19 unique host_call targets). Calls six combat-prep effect handlers ($81FC, $9323, $933A, $9351, $9368, $9814) plus the standard select/prompt cluster. Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:599A:driver_tax:Command 3 (Tax) driver. Set tax rate. Calls effect_tax ($82D6) twice — once after the rate input, once for the peasantry-reaction result. Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:5A5D:driver_send:Command 4 (Send) driver. Transfer rice/gold between own provinces. Calls effect_send ($8BE5). Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:5B7E:driver_dam:Command 5 (Dam) driver. Build dam infrastructure to raise output. Calls effect_dam ($87D8) and helper_dam_rounding ($887D). Two-effect command. Chapter 10 + 11.
NesPrgRom:5C4F:driver_pact:Command 6 (Pact) driver. Form a non-aggression pact. Diplomacy subsystem. Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:5D3D:driver_grow:Command 7 (Grow) driver. Raise province output. The fully-traced reference command (Chapter 9). Driver handles the cost (debits gold from province) and silent preconditions (header >= output blocks; gold == 0 blocks). Calls effect_grow ($87F0) for the actual stat changes.
NesPrgRom:5DC4:driver_marry:Command 8 (Marry) driver. Alliance by marriage. Costs gold (demanded by target), outcome not guaranteed. Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:61B6:driver_trade:Command 9 (Trade) driver. Trade with a passing merchant. Calls effect_trade ($8A15). Requires a merchant present. Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:65F4:driver_hire:Command 10 (Hire) driver. Recruit Men or Ninja. Thin driver — substance is in effect_hire ($A2D2). Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:6637:driver_train:Command 11 (Train) driver. Raise lord's skill against a header-derived cap. Calls effect_train ($9586). Chapter 10 + 11.
NesPrgRom:66C7:driver_view:Command 12 (View) driver. Inspect a fief; spy on others (costs gold, can fail). Heaviest non-War driver (189 insns). Calls FOUR effect handlers ($83FA, $85A7, $85EA, $A6B3) — different sub-behaviors. Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:6853:driver_build:Command 13 (Build) driver. Raise province town. Same prompt-and-apply shape as Grow. Calls effect_build ($88A6). Chapter 10 + 11. THIS SESSION: effect walked side-by-side with Grow as structural diff.
NesPrgRom:6A1F:driver_give:Command 14 (Give) driver. Charity → loyalty/morale. Touches the MOST province fields of any command — calls THREE effect handlers ($A93A, $A95E, $A9D5). Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:6AAE:driver_bribe:Command 15 (Bribe) driver. Bribe a target's fields. Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:6D67:driver_assign:Command 16 (Assign) driver. Place a retainer. Calls effect_assign ($AC11). Chapter 10 + 11.
NesPrgRom:6DB3:driver_rest:Command 17 (Rest) driver. Skip turns to recover (health/age interplay). Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:6F38:driver_map:Command 18 (Map) driver. Render the strategic map. 18 instructions, no prompt, no cost — pure display. Calls map_helper_e5f2 + $AF10. Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:6F66:driver_grant:Command 19 (Grant) driver. Set a province's policy state. Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:723E:driver_other:Command 20 (Other) driver — settings/save menu. Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:72A1:driver_pass:Command 21 (Pass) driver. End the turn. Five instructions. Chapter 11.
NesPrgRom:5F04:subhandler_9F04:Driver-table index 21. Probably reached from Other/save menu. Calls effect_subhandler_9F04 ($8B40).
NesPrgRom:5FAF:subhandler_9FAF:Driver-table index 22.
NesPrgRom:6003:subhandler_A003:Driver-table index 23. Calls effect_subhandler_A003 ($8B0A).
NesPrgRom:6068:subhandler_A068:Driver-table index 24.
NesPrgRom:6113:subhandler_A113:Driver-table index 25. Calls effect_subhandler_A113 ($A0ED).
NesPrgRom:61AF:subhandler_A1AF:Driver-table indices 26 and 33 (appears twice). Tiny stub (frame_off=0, body starts with `40 CF` = clearA + vm_return) — effectively a no-op slot.
NesPrgRom:7066:subhandler_B066:Driver-table index 27.
NesPrgRom:709D:subhandler_B09D:Driver-table index 28.
NesPrgRom:70D2:subhandler_B0D2:Driver-table index 29.
NesPrgRom:7109:subhandler_B109:Driver-table index 30.
NesPrgRom:712B:subhandler_B12B:Driver-table index 31.
NesPrgRom:714B:subhandler_B14B:Driver-table index 32.
NesPrgRom:47F0:effect_grow:Grow effect (chapter 9 reference decode). Args: arg1=record_ptr, arg2=gold_amount. Spine: guard amount<1; sqrt(output+amount); -2 (const_two); $D6B8 32-bit math; <<1; clamp to (header-output) headroom; flat-100 branch if gain/2>output else $D6DE refinement; $D70D drain LOYALTY; $D70D drain DAMS; output += gain. Returns gain/2 for driver to display.
NesPrgRom:48A6:effect_build:Build effect (this session, structural diff against effect_grow). Same five-phase shape. Differences: operates on TOWN (record+4) not OUTPUT, headroom is header-TOWN, drains WEALTH (record+14) not LOYALTY/DAMS, has a secondary TOWN bump via helper_dam_rounding ($887D).
NesPrgRom:47D8:effect_dam:Dam effect (primary). Two-step command — driver calls this AND helper_dam_rounding ($887D).
NesPrgRom:487D:helper_dam_rounding:Secondary effect used by both driver_dam and effect_build. Does integer-divide-with-rounding-up, then `field += quotient`, then calls $82AC. Produces the 'capped add' increment on top of the main sqrt-driven gain. Used twice on the lord-command menu — anywhere there's a layered increment.
NesPrgRom:42D6:effect_tax:Tax effect. Called twice from driver_tax — once for the rate-set, once for the peasantry-reaction result message (protesting/delighted).
NesPrgRom:4BE5:effect_send:Send effect. Apply rice/gold transfer between own provinces.
NesPrgRom:4CA5:effect_move:Move effect. Apply troop relocation between own provinces.
NesPrgRom:4A15:effect_trade:Trade effect (buy/sell with merchant).
NesPrgRom:62D2:effect_hire:Hire effect (recruit Men or Ninja). Chapter 11 notes 'the substance is in the callee' — this is the substance.
NesPrgRom:5586:effect_train:Train effect. Raises lord skill against header-derived cap. Chapter 10.
NesPrgRom:4D4D:effect_bribe:Bribe effect. Like Grow but pointed at a target's fields.
NesPrgRom:6C11:effect_assign:Assign effect. Places a retainer.
NesPrgRom:43FA:effect_view_a:View effect, variant A (4 sub-effects total for View — own vs others, spy variants).
NesPrgRom:45EA:effect_view_b:View effect, variant B.
NesPrgRom:45A7:effect_view_c:View effect, variant C.
NesPrgRom:66B3:effect_view_d:View effect, variant D.
NesPrgRom:693A:effect_give_a:Give effect, variant A (Give touches the most fields — 3 sub-effects).
NesPrgRom:695E:effect_give_b:Give effect, variant B.
NesPrgRom:69D5:effect_give_c:Give effect, variant C.
NesPrgRom:41FC:effect_war_a:War effect, variant A (6 combat-prep effects total).
NesPrgRom:4172:count_eligible_targets:Walks a 0xFF-terminated candidate-fief list; keeps each that passes target_eligible_by_cmd ($812F) AND province_state ($6CF7[cand]) != 0xFF; returns the COUNT of valid targets. arg3=0 count / =1 commit. The candidate FILTER for province_select_helper. Filters by ELIGIBILITY (ownership+state), not troop strength.
NesPrgRom:412F:target_eligible_by_cmd:switch(arg1=command/context code 1/2/4/6/8/15/19/255) -> for war-type modes calls is_enemy_owned ($D9B7) on candidate arg2; returns valid/0. Per-command target validity.
NesPrgRom:4DE1:dedup_owners_to_6F4F:Builds a de-duplicated-by-OWNER candidate list from a 0xFF-terminated input list into the $6F4F[] array (0xFF-terminated); returns count. Owner-uniqueness via fief_to_daimyo_map.
NesPrgRom:5323:effect_war_combat_prep_a:War combat-prep subroutine A (chapter 11).
NesPrgRom:533A:effect_war_combat_prep_b:War combat-prep subroutine B.
NesPrgRom:5351:effect_war_combat_prep_c:War combat-prep subroutine C.
NesPrgRom:5368:effect_war_combat_prep_d:War combat-prep subroutine D.
