NesPrgRom:60ED:effect_subhandler_A113:Effect called by subhandler_A113.
NesPrgRom:404C:province_select_prompt:Province selection prompt — 'select a fief' picker. Called by 7 drivers (Move, War, Send, Pact, Marry, View, Bribe). Returns the selected province index, typically into selected_province_idx ($6F5F).
NesPrgRom:479F:province_select_helper:Companion to province_select_prompt. Called by the same 7 drivers immediately before/after the prompt. Probably an initialization or post-pick state mutation.
NesPrgRom:471E:fief_info_display:Renders a fief's stat panel. Called by 3 drivers. Body at $8740-ish is a 12-iteration loop that calls $CEC4 (redraw_window) and $D134 per pass — the 12 visible province stats.
NesPrgRom:47CB:helper_87CB:Helper called by 3 drivers.
NesPrgRom:4B8F:helper_8B8F:Helper called by 2 drivers (Pact, Marry).
NesPrgRom:71A6:submenu_prompt:Submenu prompt. Called by Trade (buy/sell) and others. The 'pick from a few options' primitive.
NesPrgRom:42AC:helper_82AC:Helper called by 4 drivers. Tail of helper_dam_rounding.
NesPrgRom:4357:helper_8357:Helper called by 4 drivers.
NesPrgRom:4A4E:helper_8A4E:Helper called by 4 drivers.
NesPrgRom:43C7:helper_83C7:Helper called by 2 drivers.
NesPrgRom:6F10:map_helper_af10:Helper called by 2 drivers (Map).
NesPrgRom:3D836:cap_fief_stats:Generic per-fief stat-cap sweep. Args: arg1 = fief idx. Loops over 12 fields (gold..arms at offsets 0,2,...,22), caps each at header via min_word ($CB5E), forces negatives to 0. Post-loop: special dams cap at 100. Called from bank 0 by the season-turnover code (3 sites at $A2CF/$A4A0/$A74C) AND from bank 1 by command-post-cleanups (5+ sites). This is NOT the income-add code — it's the cleanup pass that runs before and after income is added.
NesPrgRom:4250:relations_matrix_get:[HIGH] Pure getter: returns byte $6193[arg2*54 + arg1] (the 54-stride per-fief adjacency/relations matrix; cf. clear_fief_pair_6193 $E1E7). Leading if/XOR canonicalizes index order; no side effects. arg2=row/from, arg1=col/to.
NesPrgRom:4271:relations_rng_predicate:[MED] Probabilistic predicate over the relations matrix: two rng_mod(100) rolls ($8290,$82A3), each UCMPLT against relations_matrix_get keyed by ui_helper_d772 (fief->daimyo). Returns 0/1 boolean = 1 iff EITHER roll satisfies rng<relation (OR, early-out). Caller $9046 uses it as an AI-decision gate. (Bytecode-corrected: NOT 'always returns 0'.)
NesPrgRom:4303:math32_muladddiv:[HIGH] 32-bit fixed-point mul-add-div: sign_extend->umul32->add32->sdiv32 ($8308-$8326) = floor((a*b + c)/d). Distinct from math32_3arg (no add term). The general primitive specialized by sub_8327.
NesPrgRom:4327:scale_div10_capcheck:[MED] Scales via math32_muladddiv then range-checks: computes rounded (a*b+9)/10, and if it exceeds arg3 returns -1 (0xFFFFFFFF sentinel); otherwise returns the plain floor(a*b/10) ($832C-$8356). NOT a clamp — overflow yields a sentinel, and tested value (+9 rounding) differs from returned value. Caller $B4D5 (AI command-cost eval). (Bytecode-corrected.)
NesPrgRom:4379:apply_two_grows_const1_override:[MED] Saves config const $6D63 (const_two, the Grow/Build subtrahend), forces it to 1 (=> stronger grow), calls record_apply_two_grows ($D940) on a record pair, then *(word*)arg1 -= arg2 with floor-at-0, restores $6D63, returns its prior value. Caller $95C9 (rng_mod + ui_helper_d7ea). (Bytecode-corrected: does NOT 'return 2' — returns saved $6D63; the load-bearing mechanic is the temporary const override.)
NesPrgRom:43A2:province_window_redraw_ba6f:[HIGH-structure] Redraws province window/message $BA6F via redraw_window ($CEC4); also calls ui_helper_d134 ($D134). Gated on province_ai_state[arg1] != 0xFF (arg2 forced to 0xFF otherwise). Callers effect_view_a + AI driver $B79B. The $BA6F string's exact text is unlabeled.
NesPrgRom:43D5:province_window_redraw_ba78:[HIGH-structure] Sibling of province_window_redraw_ba6f: identical mechanism (redraw_window $CEC4 + ui_helper_d134), differs only in window/message ptr $BA78. Same province_ai_state gate, same callers.
