NesPrgRom:789B:ai_per_fief_command_driver:[CONFIRMED/HIGH] Bytecode (body @ $B8A0) confirms a per-fief AI driver. Outer loop: local11 increments at $B99E/$B99D and loops back to $B8AA while ($B9A0) local11 UCMPLT $6D9D scenario_fief_count. Per iteration ($B90E): $B913 LOADR_imm2 $6F1B + local11 + BYTE_DEREF -> selecte…
NesPrgRom:AFE1:battle_init_driver:Battle-init driver (bank 2 entry, via $8000 = JMP here). Calls map_populate ($8903) at $AFFC to fill the SRAM staging buffer from ROM, then map_render_driver (via $8977 -> $885E) at $AFFF to blit staging -> PPU. Run headless via probe-map-emit.py / render-rom-to-map.py.
NesPrgRom:8903:map_populate:Tactical-map POPULATOR: expands the per-fief cell data from ROM into the SRAM staging buffer at $7BFD (11 cols x 88 stride, 5 rows of metatiles). Inputs: battle_defending_province ($6F63) + scenario_fief_count ($6D9D); source = tactical_map_cell_pool ($A57E, bank 4) via province_to_mapid_table ($F70E). Reads cells one byte at a time through syscall_memcpy_banked ($10). Verified cell-exact on Mino/Tanba/Ezo + the whole 50-fief atlas. Returns clean with only memcpy syscalls.
NesPrgRom:885E:map_render_driver:Tactical-map RENDER driver: walks the populated $7BFD staging buffer (col*88 stride) and blits each column to the PPU via syscall_ppu_blit_from_bank ($14). This is staging->PPU, NOT the populator (that's map_populate $8903). Uses host_call $CC54 for the metatile-pattern copy (exact behavior still open — ROADMAP).
NesPrgRom:8086:unpack_base5_digits_upload_blocks:[HIGH AMENDED] Dereferences packed word *($6EB1 + 2*word[$6F5B]), splits it into base-5 digits (local7..local11 via repeated /5,%5), then uploads per-digit blocks: 4 PPU uploads ($CF7C) and 4 SRAM-wrap syscalls ($CBBD), each addressed by digit*const + ROM table base ($A604..$AEAC).
NesPrgRom:822A:prompt_yes_no:[HIGH AMENDED] Modal Yes/No prompt: draws the "(Y/N)?" string, polls wait_button_edge until A(0x40) or B(0x80) is pressed, then renders the chosen response and returns the selection.
NesPrgRom:8270:set_combat_state_pair_7bf5_7bf7:[HIGH AMENDED] Setter: writes two combat-state globals mem_7BF5 = arg[+0] and mem_7BF7 = arg[+1] from its frame-local arguments, then returns.
NesPrgRom:827E:unit_record_ptr:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Computes address of a 6-byte-stride combat-unit record indexed by arg1: returns arg1*6 + $6F7D (RAM base $6F7D); +4 field is the per-unit hp/damage accumulator.
NesPrgRom:828B:unit_field_ptr_6fd0:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Returns byte-element address into 5-column table at $6FD0: addr = arg1*5 + arg2 + $6FD0 (arg1=row, arg2=column).
NesPrgRom:829A:unit_field_ptr_6fda:[HIGH CONFIRMED] 2D row-major address accessor: returns &$6FDA[arg1*5 + arg2], indexing a 5-column-wide per-unit byte table; sibling of $828B (base $6FD0, +10 bytes).
NesPrgRom:82C9:unit_word_field_ptr_6fbc:[HIGH CONFIRMED] 2D element-address accessor: returns $6FBC + arg1*10 + arg2*2 — base $6FBC, 10-byte row stride (arg1), word columns (arg2<<1); 12 combat callers index a per-unit word-field table.
NesPrgRom:82DB:test_map_cell_bits:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Boolean predicate: bounds-checks x<=10/y<=4, reads tactical cell via read_map_cell($DC88), ANDs result with mask arg3, returns whether any of those terrain/edge flag bits are set (0 on out-of-bounds).
NesPrgRom:82FF:is_no_province_selected:[HIGH AMENDED] Returns (selected_province_idx[$6F5F] == 50); 50 is the one-past-last sentinel (valid fiefs 0-49), so this is the "no/invalid province selected" guard — 12 combat/UI sites branch-skip when true.
NesPrgRom:838F:get_battle_side_province:[HIGH AMENDED] Returns defender province index ($6F63) if arg1!=0, else the attacker/selected province index ($6F5F); arg1 is a battle-side selector flag.
NesPrgRom:83A2:calc_tactical_cell_coords:[MED CONFIRMED] Computes two tactical-cell screen coordinates from a cell-field pointer and writes them via output pointers: coord1=((field+1)<<2)+((flag&1)<<1), coord2=((field - mem_6FFE*3)<<2)+10 (mem_6FFE = combat scratch base).
NesPrgRom:83C6:lookup_terrain_attr_record:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Reads a map cell's terrain byte (via read_map_cell $DC88), masks &0xFE, tests terrain bits to build a type index in local11, returns the 16-byte-stride attribute-record pointer (index<<4)+$B11E.
NesPrgRom:8488:read_button_press:[MED AMENDED] Polls the controller via poll_input ($D14E) and switches on the NES button bitmask (keys 0x02/0x20/0x50/0x80/0xA0 = dpad + Start/Sel/B/A), returning a button-press code (0 = no press); consumed by the wait-for-press debounce loop $8561.
NesPrgRom:84F7:step_coord_by_direction:[HIGH AMENDED] Moves a tactical-map position one cell in a cardinal direction: switch on dir arg (0..3, return 0 if >=4) inc/dec the x/y coords behind pointer locals 12/13, then validates via bounds-check $8F11 (rejects out-of-range, returns 0).
NesPrgRom:8792:prompt_province_selection:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Modal province-pick prompt: draws range window ("\n(%d-%d)\n" via ui_helper_d134), runs cursor province select ($D59D), draws confirm window ($D309) only for a real pick; returns picked index (local11), 0=cancel, -1=special/no-confirm.
NesPrgRom:882A:upload_map_cell_tiles:[MED CONFIRMED] Uploads one map cell's 5-unit tile block to the PPU: reads source via syscall16_sram_wrap(1, col*9+$6FE4, row*49+$9C24, 5) then ppu_upload_block_wrap(3, col*48+$1510, row*49+$9C25, 5), addresses keyed by (row,col); called per-cell from the map-render loop.
NesPrgRom:8B39:draw_combat_day_header:[HIGH AMENDED] Draws the combat window frame and renders the day-counter header string "\nDay %2d" ($B56A) during battle.
NesPrgRom:8E40:ai_score_strength_term_40pct:[MED AMENDED] Combat-AI scorer term: fetches word from $7BEA strength-table at arg*2, scales to 40% via pct_op, then pct_op-combines a caller-pushed value; returns one additive component of engagement scorer $9C88.
NesPrgRom:8E5C:ai_sum_battle_strength:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Builds the 2-slot battle-strength accumulator at $7BEA/$7BEC (attacker=selected_province vs defender=$6F63): loop1 5x sums commander/daimyo-record bytes (pointers seeded from ui_helper_d7ea=fief_to_daimyo_record_addr + $7BEA/$7BEC), loop2 7x routes by comparing 26-byte province records at idx*26+$7013; the sum feeds odds-calc $8E40 (pct_op).
NesPrgRom:8F11:is_tile_in_bounds:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Boolean bounds predicate: returns 1 iff arg1<=10 AND arg2<=4 (else 0), validating a tactical-grid (x,y) coordinate against the 11-wide x 5-tall combat tile map.
NesPrgRom:8F28:validate_dir_code_and_dispatch:[MED AMENDED] Validates a direction code (ASCII '1'-'6' = 49-54) in an AI move loop: returns 0 if code>=55, else normalizes to 0-5 (code-49) and tail-dispatches 3 packed args to $8003, returning its result as a validity flag.
NesPrgRom:813C:build_blit_fief_tile_block:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Builds a 6x6 (36-byte) fief tile-cell block — from per-fief table fief_id*36+$B144 or a frame buffer, adding a +36 tile-base to each cell — then uploads palette/blocks and blits it via ppu_blit_from_bank_wrap.
NesPrgRom:82A9:cur_unit_field_ptr_6fd0:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Thin wrapper: pushes current-unit index ($7BE4) and current-field index ($7BE8), calls unit_field_ptr_6fd0 ($828B) to return &$6FD0[unit*5 + field] in the 5-column combat field table.
NesPrgRom:82B9:cur_unit_field_ptr_6fda:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Wrapper binding current-unit ($7BE4) and current-field ($7BE8) globals into a pointer to the 5-column $6FDA field table via unit_field_ptr_6fda; exact mirror of $82A9 (which targets $6FD0).
NesPrgRom:836A:unit_damage_within_strength:[HIGH AMENDED] Predicate: returns 1 when ceil(unit damage-accum[+4]/15) <= unit strength[+2], i.e. scaled damage still within strength (unit survives); caller increments a casualty counter on the false branch.
NesPrgRom:840B:draw_tactical_cursor_region:[MED AMENDED] Draws/erases the tactical-map selection cursor: seeds col/row from combat coord pair $7BF5/$7BF7, calls calc_tactical_cell_coords ($83A2), then sweeps 16 cells (col++ with row-wrap at &3==2) emitting a draw syscall per cell; arg1==1 draws the region, else erases — callers blink it around input polling.
NesPrgRom:8544:step_coord_from_dir_code:[HIGH CONFIRMED] If dir code != 48 ('0' sentinel), decode it to a direction index via ((code-48)>>1)-1 then step the coords one cell via step_coord_by_direction ($84F7); else return 0 (no move).
NesPrgRom:87B7:draw_tactical_terrain_feature:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Per-cell tactical-map renderer: if map cell bit 2 is set, computes cell coords, looks up the terrain attribute record, picks a tile via the terrain-type byte, and blits/renders the feature tile at (coord+2) offsets.
NesPrgRom:8977:render_combat_map_screen:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Builds and uploads the tactical battle map to the PPU: 16-iter palette load from table $B55A via palette_write_wrap, PPU block upload ($CF7C), then resolves the selected fief (fief_to_mapid $DC66) and uploads its map cells (upload_map_cell_tiles $882A) twice, finishing with map_render_driver $885E on source word $6FFE.
NesPrgRom:8B8A:draw_unit_stat_field:[MED CONFIRMED] Combat-mode-gated (mem_7BFB!=2 early-return) renderer that reads UI cursor pos $7FCD/$7FCF, resolves a unit record via unit_record_ptr ($827E) and dereferences a stat field, then blits it via ui_helper_cc7b ($CC7B)/ui_helper_d134 ($D134).
NesPrgRom:8BEA:combat_unit_window_refresh:[MED CONFIRMED] Repaints the combat side's unit/info window panes: guarded by mem_7BFB==2, loops a counter drawing each unit's commander name (daimyo_name_table $77A8) plus Gold/Rice/Men stats (fmt str $B578) via unit_record_ptr/redraw_window/ui_draw_window_d2f9.
NesPrgRom:8C61:draw_unit_roster_columns:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Renders the battle unit-roster table: sets up unit-record (local9), province-record (local10, idx*26+$7013) and daimyo-record (local11) pointers, then loops 18 entries dispatching on $7FCF to advance one pointer +2 and emit a %4d/---- column-format string ($B591-$B5A2) per column, ending with the draw call $E76F at coords (20,24).
NesPrgRom:8D39:draw_combat_fief_day_header:[HIGH AMENDED] Draws the battle header banner: prints "Fief %2d" (active combat fief = [$6F63]+1) via ui_helper $CC7B/$D134, then calls draw_combat_day_header($8B39) for the "Day %2d" line.
NesPrgRom:8EF5:ai_attacker_outstrengths_defender:[HIGH CONFIRMED] AI strength gate: returns ai_score_strength_term_40pct(0,$6F81) > ai_score_strength_term_40pct(1,$6F87) after seeding via ai_sum_battle_strength — true when attacking side-0 outstrengths defending side-1.
NesPrgRom:8F55:clear_unit_combat_flags:[MED CONFIRMED] Resets combat unit flag/state: clears bit7 of [mem_7BE8+$6F65] flag byte (&127), then zeros the $6DA2-array state bytes for arg1 and arg2 indices.
NesPrgRom:8F79:test_unit_type_present_flag:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Returns 1 if bit arg2 of the unit-type-present bitfield byte[arg1+$6F65] is set, else 0; guarded by arg2<5 (5 unit types).
NesPrgRom:8F97:clear_unit_status_flag_set_field_200:[MED AMENDED] Clears flag bits in per-unit status byte at $6F65 (idx arg1) via ROM AND-mask $B5B9[arg2], then writes constant 200 (0xC8) into the unit field addressed through unit_field_ptr_6fd0/6fda.
NesPrgRom:8FC0:find_unit_slot_by_fields:[MED CONFIRMED] Scans the 5 unit slots (0..4) for one whose field tables match: returns found when unit_field_6fd0[slot]==arg2 AND unit_field_6fda[slot]==arg3; used by callers as a found/not-found predicate.
NesPrgRom:900A:wrap_index_0_2_to_zero:[HIGH AMENDED] Wraps a 0..2 index: if arg > 2 (unsigned) resets it to 0, else leaves it; returns the index. Wrap-to-zero, not saturating clamp.
NesPrgRom:9019:test_map_cell_blocked_c2:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Map-cell predicate: pushes fixed mask 0xC2 and forwards its (x,y) args to test_map_cell_bits($82DB), returning whether the cell has terrain/obstacle bits 0xC2 set.
NesPrgRom:9030:is_battleside_province_aistate5_and_not_resting:[MED AMENDED] Predicate: true iff the battle-side province (get_battle_side_province $838F) is in AI-state 5 (available/selectable marker) AND its owning daimyo has rest_turns_remaining==0 (not currently resting).
NesPrgRom:90BB:build_daimyo_province_list:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Builds the list of province indices owned by one daimyo: target_owner=ui_helper_d772(arg); scans province bytes, skips province_state_is_FF, appends indices whose owner==target to a buffer, 0xFF-terminates, then writes it to scratch $6F4F via syscall16_sram_wrap(8,$6F4F,&buf,2).
NesPrgRom:9675:select_quadrant_damage_by_direction:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Picks one of the 4 precomputed damage words 6FF6/6FF8/6FFA/6FFC by attack direction: |dx| vs |dy| (province coords B0BA[x]/B0EC[y] of selected vs defending province, abs via cb4c) selects axis, then sign of dominant axis picks the word; early-returns 6FF6 if no province selected or 7BE8 set.
NesPrgRom:9C69:ai_strength_term_gated_table_word:[MED AMENDED] AI strength-score term: if wrap_index_0_2_to_zero(idxA) > wrap_index_0_2_to_zero(idxB) returns the word from the unit_word_field_ptr_6fbc ($82C9) table, else 0; one conditional addend in the $9C88 strength-sum chain.
NesPrgRom:830B:apply_unit_damage_over_30:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Per-side damage applier: reads unit_record[+4] accumulator, computes /30 (whole units) and %30 (carried remainder), decrements the strength/men array by the quotient clamped at >=0, redraws the stat field; loops both battle sides.
NesPrgRom:8561:wait_button_press_debounced:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Blinking-cursor debounced input wait: toggles tactical cursor, polls read_button_press in a 100-iter loop until a button is pressed, waits for release, then returns the pressed button value.
NesPrgRom:8D5D:draw_combat_roster_window:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Composes and renders the combat unit-roster window: draws window chrome via UI primitives, prints both battle-side title strings (index*const + table base $77A8) using is_no_province_selected/$6F63 to pick the source, runs an 18-slot switch loop, then draws the two roster columns via draw_unit_roster_columns(0/1).
NesPrgRom:8FEC:find_unit_at_tile:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Loops both battle sides (idx 0..1) calling find_unit_slot_by_fields to test whether any unit occupies the given tile coords; returns early on the first match (tile-occupied predicate).
NesPrgRom:910C:prompt_hit_any_key_return_button:[HIGH AMENDED] Draws a "Hit any key" prompt window, blocks on wait_button_edge, then redraws/restores UI; returns the captured button-edge code (caller $912B tests ==2 to cancel).
NesPrgRom:91A1:prompt_select_province_from_list:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Cursor-prompts a province pick via select_province_by_cursor($6D9D,$61), converts to 0-based, scans the $FF-terminated province byte-list at $6F4F for membership; returns the matched index or 255 if pick==0 or not in list.
NesPrgRom:91D5:distribute_damage_across_unit_types:[HIGH CONFIRMED] For each of 2 battle sides, splits a stack's accumulated damage (unit[+4]) across the 5 unit-type word columns at $6FBC (base+side*10) proportionally to per-fief unit counts (province*5+$76A9) via pct_op, sets the all-types flag $6F65[side]|=31, runs a remainder pass to place leftover damage, and clears the presence flag ($8F97) for any emptied type.
NesPrgRom:929C:reset_unit_field_grid_to_200:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Fills the 5x2 unit-field grid ($6FD0 and $6FDA tables, cols 0..4 x rows 0..1) with the constant 200 (0xC8) during battle-state init.
NesPrgRom:936A:draw_combat_ui_string_b196:[MED CONFIRMED] Displays fixed message string $B626 (message_display), then increments a local counter, indexes word pointer-table $B196 by it, and passes the dereferenced string pointer to ui_helper_d134 to draw a combat-UI text line.
NesPrgRom:9387:draw_unit_label_b627:[MED AMENDED] Draws the "unit %d\n%s" header (string $B627) for the current unit via ui_helper_d134: %d = unit index $7BE4+1, %s = word from 3-entry label table $F9AF at (($7BE4+1)%3)<<1; used in the per-unit give-orders UI.
NesPrgRom:93AA:announce_battle_outcome_retreat_or_won:[MED AMENDED] Battle-end resolution: determines which side ($6F63 defending vs $6F57 other) retreated vs survived, looks up the daimyo name, and displays "%s has retreated"/"%s hung on to the end and won"; runs province-AI-state/unit-damage/unit-type checks with UI redraws.
NesPrgRom:95BE:draw_tactical_cursor_region_arg0:[MED AMENDED] Thin wrapper: pushes constant 0 and calls draw_tactical_cursor_region ($840B) — draws the tactical cursor/cell region for the non-arg1==1 path; not phase-gated.
NesPrgRom:960E:is_cell_valid_for_phase:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Pure boolean predicate: returns 1 (valid) unless cell/index arg1 falls in the range forbidden by combat phase mem_$6FFE — phase0 arg1>=5, phase1 arg1>=8, phase2 arg1>5 each return 0.
NesPrgRom:9647:find_free_tactical_placement_cell:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Scans the 5x11 tactical grid (local11 rows 0..10 x local10 cols 0..4) calling test_map_cell_bits(row,col,32) per cell; on the first cell with bit-32 clear, writes row->*arg1 and col->*arg2 and returns early (finds first unoccupied placement cell).
NesPrgRom:970A:is_coord_in_combat_rect:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Pure predicate: returns 1 iff arg1(x) < $6FF6 and arg1 <= $6FFA and arg2(y) < $6FF8 and arg2 <= $6FFC, i.e. coordinate is inside the combat bounding box ($6FF6/$6FFA = x limits, $6FF8/$6FFC = y limits); else 0.
NesPrgRom:97F8:test_cur_unit_slot_present:[HIGH CONFIRMED] Thin wrapper: pushes current-unit/field globals mem_7BE4/mem_7BE8 to test_unit_type_present_flag($8F79), returns its 0/1 result; used as the unit-slot loop-continuation guard in $9810/$9865/$99D2/$9A18.
NesPrgRom:9954:rng_search_combat_rect_for_unit_cell:[MED AMENDED] Randomized rectangle search over the combat target area (bounds = quadrant scratch $6FFA x $6FFC): two rng_mod(2) seeds (local7,local6) bias per-axis step direction, switch on arg1 dir-code zeroes one/both axes; inner loop tests each cell via sub_98FE (find_unit_slot_by_fields) and returns early after calling sub_9810 on the first hit.
NesPrgRom:9BB4:ai_terrain_strength_term:[HIGH CONFIRMED] AI battle-strength term: reads the unit's map cell ($DC88) at its 6fd0/6fda position, masks $00FE and tests terrain bits (32/16/8) to decrement a class index, then returns pct_op($D70D, word[$B9C2 + idx*2] via 6fbc) * 3 — a terrain-typed strength contribution.
NesPrgRom:9C04:ai_province_stat_diff_term:[HIGH CONFIRMED] AI strength term: over 3 consecutive province word-fields, sums positive (side9-side8) cross-province stat advantage as pct_op(diff/100 weighted by $6fbc table word); returns sum*3.
NesPrgRom:9DA8:reduce_defending_province_town_chaos:[MED AMENDED] Tests map-cell bit 8 at current unit pos; computes defending-province record ptr ($6F63*26+$7005 = town field @+4) and either zeroes town (if town <= computed threshold) or saturating-reduces it by a pct_op/math32-scaled amount, then shows "town is in complete chaos!" + ui_draw_window_d31a.
NesPrgRom:A01A:unit_type_count_gt3_and_equals_arg1:[HIGH AMENDED] Counts how many of 5 unit-type slots are present (test_unit_type_present_flag on $7BE8); returns true iff count>3 AND (count-1)==arg1.
NesPrgRom:1257E:tactical_map_cell_pool:Per-fief tactical-map cell data, ~33+ maps of 55 bytes each. The live per-cell metatile source map_populate ($8903) reads one byte at a time, indexed as $A57E + province_to_mapid_table[province]*55. NOT a directly-renderable flat table (that older interpretation, in render-atlas.py, was the disproven dead-end) — correct path is to RUN $8903, not read this flat. Session 2026-05-30.
